					<description><![CDATA[<p>Series F Expansion Strengthens Global Weather Intelligence Infrastructure Tomorrow.io Raises $35M in additional Series F funding to accelerate its global expansion strategy. The round brings the company’s total Series F</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/tomorrow-io-raises-35m-ai-weather-intelligence-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Tomorrow.io Raises $35M to Expand AI Weather Intelligence Infrastructure</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Series F Expansion Strengthens Global Weather Intelligence Infrastructure</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tomorrow.io Raises $35M in additional Series F funding to accelerate its global expansion strategy. The round brings the company’s total Series F financing to $210 million. The Boston based company builds AI powered weather intelligence infrastructure designed for enterprise resilience. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It focuses on transforming atmospheric data into real time operational intelligence that supports decision making across critical industries worldwide. The latest investment was backed by Pitango and its partner Harel Insurance. Existing investors Stonecourt Capital and HarbourVest Partners also participated in the extension round. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The continued participation reflects strong conviction in Tomorrow.io’s long term infrastructure value. It also signals investor confidence in the company’s positioning within AI driven climate intelligence systems that are becoming increasingly essential for global operations. Tomorrow.io integrates space technology, advanced forecasting models, and generative AI into a unified platform.  </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The system processes large scale atmospheric data and converts it into actionable insights. These insights help organisations respond faster to environmental disruption. The platform is already used by major enterprises across aviation, logistics, energy, and government sectors where operational timing is critical and weather uncertainty directly impacts performance and cost efficiency.  </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s resilience platform is designed to function as infrastructure rather than a standalone tool. It supports continuous decision making across global supply chains. It also enables predictive risk management at scale. This positions Tomorrow.io within a growing category of AI infrastructure companies focused on real world environmental intelligence.</span></p>
<h2><b>DeepSky Satellite Constellation and AI Forecasting Expansion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A major focus of the new funding is the acceleration of DeepSky, Tomorrow.io’s AI native satellite constellation. DeepSky is designed to improve global weather observation by deploying a network of proprietary satellites. These satellites collect high resolution atmospheric data in real time. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The system is built to reduce reliance on fragmented third party weather datasets and instead create a unified global observation layer controlled by the platform itself. The DeepSky initiative is closely integrated with Tomorrow.io’s generative AI forecasting engine. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This combination allows the system to process satellite inputs and generate predictive models with higher accuracy and speed. It also enables continuous learning loops where data from space improves forecasting performance over time. The goal is to create a self improving weather intelligence system capable of adapting to changing global conditions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company is also expanding its broader space infrastructure. This includes enhancements to data transmission pipelines, orbital coordination systems, and AI based modelling frameworks. These improvements are intended to support large scale deployment and ensure real time delivery of weather intelligence across multiple regions simultaneously. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tomorrow.io is positioning DeepSky as a foundational layer for global weather intelligence. It is intended to serve not only commercial industries but also government and critical infrastructure operators. The expansion reflects a long term strategy to merge space based observation with AI driven decision systems into a single operational framework.</span></p>
<h2><b>Enterprise Adoption and Global Operational Resilience Demand<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_201367" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201367" class="size-full wp-image-201367" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/a-futuristic-neon-lit-visualization-of-g_VQpzjG31XfqAApMDGKz4jQ_0lxUNUMmSGOMnjArF9V_og_cover.png" alt="" width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-201367" class="wp-caption-text">Enterprises embed AI weather intelligence directly into operations, enabling faster decisions, reduced disruption, and proactive risk management in an increasingly volatile climate. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More and more Fortune 500 companies—especially those in aviation, logistics, energy, transportation, and the public sector—are turning to Tomorrow.io. They face high risk and uncertainty, so accurate forecasting is essential for smooth operations, fewer disruptions, and better efficiency as weather grows extreme. That’s where Tomorrow.io steps in.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Companies use the platform not just for planning and scheduling, but also for making on-the-fly adjustments when things start to shift. It’s not just about seeing a storm coming; it’s about spotting problems before they hit, and steering clear of costly delays or breakdowns in the supply chain. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This kind of insight means they can allocate people and resources more intelligently and avoid scrambling after the damage is already done. As climate change throws more curveballs, demand for tech that actively builds resilience is climbing fast. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">You can see the trend—businesses want systems that don’t just crunch numbers, but blend predictive insight with real-time information. Tomorrow.io taps right into this need by plugging environmental data straight into operational workflows, so decisions happen faster and with less guesswork. The platform feeds the right information directly to the teams that need it.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tomorrow.io doesn’t just sell software—it offers core infrastructure. That’s a big deal because, instead of being a tool people sometimes check, it becomes a live, embedded part of daily operations. For these companies, weather intelligence isn’t an afterthought anymore. It’s wired right into the way they work.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/cosmico-raises-e12m-future-of-work/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Cosmico Raises €12M To Expand Future Of Work Marketplace</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Investor Conviction and AI Driven Resilience Infrastructure Vision</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors continue to view Tomorrow.io as a foundational infrastructure company in the AI and climate intelligence space. Pitango highlighted the company’s long term mission and its role in building critical systems for global adaptation. The continued investment reflects a belief that weather intelligence will become a core component of enterprise infrastructure over the next decade.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CEO Shimon Elkabetz emphasised that weather remains one of the most powerful yet underutilised forces in global decision making. He stated that Tomorrow.io was built to change how organisations interact with environmental data. The goal is to transform raw atmospheric information into real time intelligence that can directly influence operational behaviour across industries.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tomorrow.io is also developing agentic AI systems designed to automate decision responses. These systems use live environmental data to trigger operational actions without human intervention. This represents a shift from predictive analytics toward autonomous operational intelligence. It also aligns with broader industry trends toward AI driven enterprise automation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tomorrow.io continues to expand its vision of resilience infrastructure. It combines space based observation, generative AI, and enterprise </span><a href="https://www.workato.com/the-connector/software-integration/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">software integration</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> into a unified system. This positions the company at the intersection of climate intelligence, artificial intelligence, and global operational infrastructure.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/tomorrow-io-raises-35m-ai-weather-intelligence-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Tomorrow.io Raises $35M to Expand AI Weather Intelligence Infrastructure</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
