										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">AI trading bots are increasingly used by new traders to explore automated trading workflows before using more advanced strategy setups. In 2026, users are not only looking for advanced trading dashboards. Many users look for platforms that provide beginner-friendly onboarding, automated execution tools, strategy templates, and trial access. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A good </span><b>free AI trading bot</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> should help users understand how automated trading works before they move into more advanced settings. Many entry-level trading platforms offer trial credits, demo environments, bot testing tools, strategy templates, or limited-time access to automation features. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This article reviews five automated trading platforms that provide trial or free-access options for testing AI trading bots in 2026. </span></p>
