</table>
<h2><b>How Free AI Trading Bots Work </b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A </span><b>free AI trading bot</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is an automated trading tool that lets users test bot-based trading without paying for a full plan immediately. Some platforms provide a free trial. Some offer trial credits. Others provide demo trading, free templates, or limited bot access.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The goal is simple: help users understand automation before committing to more advanced trading tools.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In crypto and stock trading, AI bots can support market monitoring, signal tracking, DCA strategies, grid trading, automated execution, portfolio actions, and rule-based workflows. The best platforms make these tools easier to test from the beginning.</span></p>
<h2><b>1. BitsStrategy</b></h2>
<p><a href="https://bitsstrategy.com/?src=BS131" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><b>New users may receive trial credit after registration.</b></a></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">BitsStrategy is designed for users interested in a more managed approach to automated AI trading. The platform emphasizes AI-powered trading workflows, managed automation, quantitative trading models, and simplified onboarding for newer users. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">BitsStrategy’s website presents a free daily trial plan using $50 credit, and recent announcements have described new-user trial credits for experiencing the platform’s AI automated trading process.</span></p>
<p><b>Free Trial Option:</b><b><br />
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> BitsStrategy offers a trial-credit-style entry point for users who want to experience AI automated trading before using larger plans.</span></p>
<p><b>Key Features:</b></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fully automated AI trading workflow</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Managed strategy execution</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Setup process designed to reduce manual configuration requirements </span></li>
</ul>
<p><b>Best First Test:</b><b><br />
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Users can begin with a trial or free-access option to observe how the automated trading workflow functions. </span></p>
<p><b>Beginner Trial Guide:</b><b><br />
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Register an account, review the available AI trading plans, activate a trial option, and monitor how the system reports trading activity.</span></p>
<h2><b>2. 3Commas</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">3Commas is a widely used automated trading platform that supports customizable bot settings and exchange-connected workflows. It supports DCA bots, Grid bots, Signal Bot tools, TradingView automation, and exchange API connections.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">3Commas states that users can create a free account, and new users are offered a 7-day free trial of selected paid plans after signing up and entering valid payment details. Its FAQ also says new users receive a time-limited trial subscription to test the platform’s trading tools.</span></p>
<p><b>Free Trial Option:</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">3Commas offers a 7-day free trial for new users.</span></p>
<p><b>Key Features:</b></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">DCA, Grid, and Signal Bot automation</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">TradingView and exchange-connected workflows</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bot customization features for users managing more advanced trading workflows </span></li>
</ul>
<p><b>Best First Test:</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Start with a simple DCA Bot or Grid Bot before testing advanced Signal Bot strategies.</span></p>
<p><b>Beginner Trial Guide:</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Create an account, connect one supported exchange, choose one simple bot type, and test conservative settings during the trial period.</span></p>
<h2><b>3. Cryptohopper</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cryptohopper is a cloud-based trading bot platform that includes automated crypto trading tools, DCA features, copy trading, and strategy templates. It is useful for users who want to test automation without keeping a computer running all day.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cryptohopper promotes a free start option on its official website, while its app listing describes a 3-day free trial for users who want to experience its crypto trading bot.</span></p>
<p><b>Free Trial Option:</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cryptohopper offers a free account/start-free option and has promoted a 3-day free trial through its mobile app listing.</span></p>
<p><b>Key Features:</b></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cloud-based crypto bot automation</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">AI tools, DCA, trailing, and copy trading</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Strategy templates for different user levels</span></li>
</ul>
<p><b>Best First Test:</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Try a template-based bot before customizing indicators or copy trading settings.</span></p>
<p><b>Beginner Trial Guide:</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Create a free account, explore templates, connect an exchange when ready, and test basic automation before moving into advanced strategies.</span></p>
<h2><b>4. Bitsgap</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bitsgap is an automated crypto trading platform that combines trading bots, AI insights, demo trading, and multi-exchange management. The platform supports Grid, DCA, and futures-style bot workflows across connected exchanges. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bitsgap states that it offers a 7-day PRO plan trial with no credit card required. Its demo trading page also promotes a free demo account with demo funds for users who want market experience before using live capital.</span></p>
<p><b>Free Trial Option:</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bitsgap offers a 7-day PRO trial and demo trading access.</span></p>
<p><b>Key Features:</b></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Grid, DCA, and futures bot tools</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Demo trading environment</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Multi-exchange automation and portfolio control</span></li>
</ul>
<p><b>Best First Test:</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Use demo trading or a Grid Bot to see how automated range-based trading works.</span></p>
<p><b>Beginner Trial Guide:</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Start with the demo account, test one bot on a major crypto pair, review the bot’s trade history, and only then explore live settings.</span></p>
<h2><b>5. TradeSanta</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">TradeSanta focuses on simplified crypto bot automation workflows. It supports Grid and DCA strategies, long and short bots, risk management tools, stop-loss settings, trailing stop loss, TradingView stop signals, and take-profit targets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">TradeSanta’s pricing page states that all new users can enjoy a 3-day free trial of the Maximum package. Its platform also highlights automated crypto bots for Grid and DCA-style strategies.</span></p>
<p><b>Free Trial Option:</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">TradeSanta offers a 3-day free trial for new users.</span></p>
<p><b>Key Features:</b></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Grid and DCA trading bots</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Long and short bot support</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Stop loss, trailing stop loss, and take-profit tools</span></li>
</ul>
<p><b>Best First Test:</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Start with a basic Grid or DCA bot on a liquid trading pair.</span></p>
<p><b>Beginner Trial Guide:</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Create an account, connect a supported exchange, launch one simple bot, and focus on understanding the settings before adding more strategies.</span></p>
<h2><b>Comparing Free AI Trading Bot Platforms for Beginners </b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The right platform depends on how much control the user wants.</span></p>
